<p><b>Erich Seligmann</b><sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> <b>Fromm</b> (March 23, 1900 â March 18, 1980) was an internationally renowned <a href="/wiki/Social_psychology" title="Social psychology">social psychologist</a>, psychoanalyst, and <a href="/wiki/Humanism" title="Humanism">humanistic</a> <a href="/wiki/Philosophy" title="Philosophy">philosopher</a>. He was associated with what became known as the <a href="/wiki/Frankfurt_School" title="Frankfurt School">Frankfurt School</a> of <a href="/wiki/Critical_theory" title="Critical theory">critical theory</a>.</p>
